title.narrative: Mexico Savings & Rural Finance (BANSEFI) Project - Phase II

description.narrative: The objective of the Project is to assist the Borrower in strengthening the SCI sector with SCIs which are compliant with the Popular Savings and Credit Law, financially viable, operationally effective, managerially sound, technologically upgraded, and providing an enhanced level of outreach and access to financial services by the underserved Mexican populations.

condition.narrative: Establish a fee-for-service regime for the technology platform services offered to the entities in the sector
Maintain an implelmentation team with appropriate skill-mix, qualifications, and experience
Monitor the performance of the TA providers and verify compliance with agreed action targets

title.narrative: The sector membership in the cooperative entities increases from 4 million to about 9 million.

baseline.value: At start of this project, the membership was about 4.1 million at the level of the SCI entities and BANSEFI branches

target.value: The sector has about 9 million members by December 2009

actual.value: Membership of the sector is about 10.1 million

comment.narrative: This number includes 8.6 million members of SCIs + 1.5 million Bansefi but does not include some 9.5 Oportunidades beneficiaries.

title.narrative: About 200 entities assisted by the project either certified by CNBV (the regulatory agency), or identified for liquidation

baseline.value: 370 entities already being assisted under the parallel BANSEFI Phase I project

target.value: 45 new entities received TA; TA completed for all Phase I entities; in both cases, entities either certified or identified forliquidation

actual.value: 517 entities assisted. 112 entities certified, 70 identified for liquidation or merger. 43 considered fit for certification.

comment.narrative: The institutions certified cover 75% of the sector in terms of assets and members. This value is expected to reach 90% by the endof 2012. Because of changes in the law, 210 institutions are no longer required to obtain certification as they are below thelegal threshold.

title.narrative: Procedures for liquidation of identified unviable entities initiated by the government

baseline.value: About 25-30 entities expected to be liquidated/ merged. Exact number tobe known after the TA component completed. Atstart-of-project no entity has been identitifed for liquidation

target.value: Identified entities either liquidated or in the process of liquidation

comment.narrative: Work is expected to accelerate, due to the Law deadline to request certification by December 2012, but whether this objective willbe achieved will depend on whether this deadline set by the law will be enforced.

title.narrative: Deposit Protection Fund established for the SCI sector

baseline.value: No deposit protection fund exists for the SCI sector at start-of-project

target.value: A deposit protection fund established with "seed" contribution from the government to start with, and additional contributionsfrommember entities

actual.value: There are twoprotection funds: onefor cooperatives andanother one forSOFIPOS. Theywere established byBANSEFI as trusteeinDecember 2010.The entities arealready depositingtheir protection fundfees.

title.narrative: Documentation for certification (or recommendation for liquidation) prepared for the participating entities and submitted to CNBV

baseline.value: No documentation existed as this is required under the new law for certification

target.value: Documentation relating to all entities completed and forwarded to CNBV for certification

actual.value: Documentation for certification prepared for all participating entities that sought certification (112 entities)

title.narrative: Technology platform being funded under the project through BANSEEFI is embraced by about 100 SCI entities

baseline.value: Some form of platform is available in very few, large entities mostly for accounting; none integrate the accounting, financialmanagement, regulatory reporting and financial products services

target.value: At least 45% market penetration is achieved: about 100 entities in the consolidated SCI sector embrace the platform

comment.narrative: This number includes all entities that use the platform for distribution ofgovernment transfers,remittancesandcorrespondentbanking. About 90 institutions have adopted the Core Banking while the other institutions (282) use variouselements, including La@Redde la Gente or the Oportunidades program.

title.narrative: Technology platform developed under the project tested, validated, and endorsed by the SCI sector entities

baseline.value: There is no integrated technology platform in any of the entities

target.value: The technology platform is rolled out nationally to all entities requesting this facility

actual.value: Technology platformhas been rolled outnationally to allentities requestingthis facility.

title.narrative: The auxiliary supervision process carried out by the Supervision Committees, and overseen by CNBV, are satisfactory

baseline.value: Under the Phase I, some Supervision Committes have been established; however, knowledge needs to be updated and the committeesneedrecertification. CNBV needs international practices knowledge

target.value: Supervision Committees and CNBV functioning efficiently and effectively, monitoring the entities in the consolidated SCI sector

comment.narrative: With the new cooperative law, one expects to see a restructuring of the supervision structure. While some existing committees maydisintegrate, new ones at the regional level will be formed. The training and capacity building of the supervisory cadre under theproject will continue to benefit the sector.
